spans.text: to whom greatness rightly understood , Is but a larger power of being good
thy loved Philosophy resigned , No care

the happy meed , To favoured man by smiling heaven decreed
On flowery couches slumbers life away
Fair olives bloom , or verdant laurels
to review a life in honour spent , And painful merit paid with sweet content
to be possessed , That only can improve and crown the rest — Permit thy friend this secret to reveal , Which thy own heart perhaps would better tell ; The point to which our sweetest passions move

that sooths the troubled breast , Friend to our health , and author of our rest , Bids every gloomy vexing passion fly , And tunes each jarring string to harmony
of Love inspires More pleasing thoughts
Some beauteous image well imprinted there

some fair eyes , my friend , thy bosom fire With pleasing pangs of ever gay desire
Hear what the inspiring Muses bid me tell , For Heaven

Distinguished only by their softer dress : Thy greatness she , or thy retreat shall share , Sweeten tranquillity , or soften care : Her smiles the taste of every joy shall raise , And add new pleasure to renown and praise ; Till charmed you own the truth my verse would prove , That Happiness is near allied to Love
